1. e4 c6 (1... e5 2. Bc4 (2. Nf3 f6?? 3. Nxe5!) 2... Nc6 3. Qh5 Nf6 4. Qxf7#) 2. c4 d5 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Nc3?! { Gives Black a tempo, gives Black space. } (4. exd5 Nf6 (4... Qxd5?! { Developing the Q too early. } 5. Nc3) 5. Bb5+ Nbd7 6. Nc3 a6 7. Bc4 b5 8. Bb3 b4) 4... d4 5. Nce2 e5 6. Qb3?! { Developing the Q too early. } (6. d3 Nc6 7. a3) 6... Nc6 (6... Nf6!) (6... Be6 7. Qxb7 Nd7) 7. f4 (7. Nf3 Nf6) 7... f6? (7... Nf6! 8. fxe5 Nxe5 9. Qb5+ Nc6) (7... exf4) 8. Nf3 (8. fxe5 fxe5) 8... d3 9. Nc3 Nb4 10. Nd5 (10. Kd1 Nc2 (10... exf4!?) 11. Rb1 Ne7 12. fxe5 fxe5 13. Bxd3 Qxd3 14. Qxc2) 10... Nc2+ 11. Kd1 Nxa1 12. Qxd3 Bd6 13. Qc3 Bg4? { Up material  coordinate / simplify, trade and win the endgame. } (13... Ne7 14. Bb5+ Bd7 15. Bxd7+ Qxd7 16. Nxe7 Bxe7 17. b3 exf4 18. Qxa1 O-O) 14. Bb5+ Kf7? { Exposing the king. } (14... Bd7! 15. Bxd7+ Qxd7 16. fxe5 Rc8 17. Qd4 Nc2 18. Qxa7 fxe5 (18... Bc5)) (14... Kf8! { King is much safer here. } 15. b3 Ne7 16. Nxe7 Qxe7 17. Qxa1 exf4) 15. d4 (15. Ke1 Ne7 16. Kd1 Re8 17. Ke1 Kg8 18. Kd1 Kh8) 15... Ne7?! { No need to do anything crazy. } (15... exd4! 16. Qxd4 Ne7 (16... Bxf3+ 17. gxf3 Ne7) 17. b3 Nxd5 18. exd5 (18. Qxd5+ Be6 19. Qd4 Bc5 20. Qxd8 Rhxd8+) 18... Bxf3+ 19. gxf3 Qb6) 16. fxe5 Rc8 17. Qd3 Nxd5 18. Bc4 fxe5 (18... Bxf3+ 19. gxf3 fxe5 20. Bxd5+ Kf8) 19. Bxd5+ Kg6? (19... Kf8 20. Rf1 Qc7) (19... Ke8) 20. h3! Rxc1+? { Panic. } (20... Qc7! 21. Bd2 Qc2+ 22. Qxc2 Bxf3+ 23. gxf3 Nxc2 24. Rg1+ Kf6 (24... Kh5) 25. Bg5+ Kg6) 21. Kxc1 Qc7+ 22. Kb1 Rc8 23. Nh4+ Kf6 24. Rf1+ Kg5 25. Qe3+ Kxh4 26. hxg4 Qc2+ 27. Kxa1 Qxg2 28. Qe1+ Kg5 29. Rf5+ Kxg4 30. Qd1+ Kh4 31. Rh5+ Kg3 32. Rg5+ Kf2 33. Rxg2+ Kxg2 34. Qd2+ Kg3 35. dxe5 Bxe5 36. Qg5+ Kf3 37. Qf5+ Bf4 38. Qxc8 h5 39. Qh3+ Kf2 40. e5 g5 41. Qf3+ Kg1 42. Qg2# { 1-0 White wins. } 1-0


