1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 Qe7 4. Nf3?! { My prep is d4 not Nf3. Still an ok move but I left theory first. } 4... Nxe4 5. Be2 g6 { Makes a bit of sense because he wants to develop bishop somehow and castle but definitely didn't seem like the correct way to develop for him. } 6. O-O Bg7 7. Nc3 { I liked the position after Nxc3, dxc3 since it removes his most active piece while opening up my bishop. } 7... Nxc3 8. dxc3 O-O 9. Re1 { Putting my rook on the same file as his queen seemed like a no brainer. I considered Bf4 and Bg5 a lot tho and couldn't really tell if either was better than moving rook. } 9... d6 10. h3 { Didn't want to allow his bishop to develop to g4. In hindsight not an accurate move as I can just keep developing and Bg4 would have posed no threats to me. } 10... Qf6 11. Bg5 { Was considering Bg5 for a while now and him moving his queen there means he will waste two tempi. } 11... Qf5 12. Qd2 { Simple idea of potentially attacking his bishop on g7 with Bh6 in the future and also further developing by moving my queen off her starting position and connecting my rooks. } 12... f6 { Did no see this move coming. In my mind the bishop being attacked was going to h6 anyway and now he has just weakened his king further. } 13. Bd3 { I thought this move put my bishop on a better square for free since his queen doesn't have any good moves from here. } 13... Qd5 14. b3 { Liked this idea because now he has to waste another tempo moving king or queen. Plus this remains a threat for the future as I saw later. (Chess.com gave it a !!) } 14... Kh8 15. Bh6 { Finally time to move bishop. I didn't see any other threats. In addition I calculated both Bxh6 Qxh6 followed by Re7 soon with a strong attack on the king and if black wastes time Bxg7+ Kxg7, Re7+ Kh8 (since g8 loses to Bc4), Qh6 again with strong attack on king. } 15... Bf5 (15... Bxh6 16. Qxh6 { [%cal Gh6f8] } 16... Nd7 17. Re7) (15... Bd7 16. Bxg7+ Kxg7 17. Re7+ Kh8 (17... Kg8 18. Bc4) 18. Qh6) 16. Bxg7+ Kxg7 17. Re7+ { As mentioned on move 15, strong initiative against black's king. } 17... Rf7 18. Rxf7+ Kxf7?? { Ouch! } (18... Qxf7 19. Bxf5 gxf5 20. Re1) 19. Bc4 Qxc4 20. bxc4 { Ugly pawns < Queen } 20... Nd7 21. Qd5+ { Free pawn } 21... Be6 22. Qxb7 Rb8 23. Qxc7 { Free pawn plus pin on knight } 23... Ke7 24. Re1 { More pins! } 1-0


