1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. Ng5 d5 5. exd5 Nxd5 { Always happy when this happens. } 6. Nxf7 Kxf7 7. Qf3+ Qf6 { I don't think I've ever seen this specific move before. But I thought for a minute and realized that after Bd5 I will transpose to the line I know. } (7... Ke8 8. Bxd5 Qf6 9. Bxc6+ Qxc6 10. Qxc6+) 8. Bxd5+ Ke8 9. Bxc6+ Qxc6 10. Qxc6+ bxc6 { And this is just a great position for me. Up 1 pawn plus doubled pawns on the c file. } { [%csl Bc6,Bc7] } 11. d3 { Thought about castling but since there is no rush I felt like this move made sense to allow my bishop to come out if needed. } 11... h6 { This seemed slow. Very slow. I already had a better position and if he let's me get free moves everything will start falling. } 12. O-O Bc5 13. Nd2?? { Here I consider this move a blunder. The reason why is that I wanted to play Re1 but I thought that after 13. ... O-O black would get his king out of the way and create an attack on my f2 pawn. So to avoid this I went for Nd2 with the intention of blocking the rook's view with Nf3. Only problem being that black can't castle! If I had played Re1 then black playing ... Rf8 would simply lose him another pawn. } 13... Rf8 14. Nf3 Bd6 { Only sensible move in my opinion but that pawn was going to fall at some point. } 15. Re1 Kf7 { This was a surprise. I had calculated 15. ... Rf5 } (15... Rf5 16. Nd4 Rh5 17. Nxc6) 16. Nxe5+ Bxe5 17. Rxe5 Kg8 18. Bd2 Rb8 19. Bc3 Rf7 20. Rae1 Bd7 21. h3 { Wanted to avoid any back rank problems. } 21... Rb5 22. Re7 Rbf5 23. Rxf7 { I thought trading was only going to help me because I had a clear static advantage. } 23... Rxf7 24. Be5 Re7 { I saw this and thought that after Kf1 it's not a problem and the c7 pawn is threatened again. } 25. Kf1 Be6 26. Bxc7 Kf7 (26... Rxc7 27. Rxe6) 27. Bd6 { Now I had to move my bishop and I couldn't see why anything else was better than Bd6. } 27... Rd7 28. Bc5 Bxa2 { I thought this wasn't a threat from a distance because of b3 and then Ra1. } 29. b3 Rd5 { This was the only move I thought gave him a chance. But instead of defending my bishop in any way I just opted for the trade of bishops with Ra1 right away. I think in hindsight this was the move I would most want to change. The rook endgame ended up being much harder than I thought it would. } 30. Ra1 Rxc5 31. Rxa2 a5 32. g4 g5 33. Kg2 Kf6 34. Kg3 Ke5 35. h4 gxh4+ 36. Kxh4 { Here I thought I was still doing great. } 36... Kf4 { This move I missed tho and it definitely seemed a bit scary. } 37. d4 Rg5 38. c4 Rxg4+ 39. Kh5 Kf3 40. Kxh6 Rxd4 { At this point I was very scared. I thought this might very well be a draw. } 41. Kg5 Rd3 42. Rb2 c5 43. Kf5 Rc3 44. Ke5 Rd3 45. Ke6 { Him repeating moves didn't seem right tho because like this I can slowly bring my king closer. I was looking at Ra2 followed by trading the a pawn for the b pawn but then winning the c pawn. And by first going Ke6 I force him to move his rook off the 3rd rank which buys me a tempo. } 45... Rd4 46. Ra2 Rd3 { Now I can go for the same idea and black is a move behind. } 47. Rxa5 Rxb3 48. Rxc5 Kxf2 49. Rd5 Rb4 50. c5 Rc4 51. Kd6 Ke3 52. c6 Ke4 { After this move by him I regretted not playing Kd7 instead of Kd6. I thought this might be a draw since I can't advance my pawn: } 53. Rh5 Kf4 54. Rh6 Kg5 55. Re6 Kf5 56. Kd7 { This whole rook reroute allowed me to advance my king as I didn't see a way to make that happen with the rook on e5. } 56... Rc5 57. Rd6 Ke5 { Here I finally felt like I could actually see the win. } 58. Rd1 { With this move his king will never get close to the pawn and his rook will never check my king. I definitely wondered if I could have reached something similar earlier... } 58... Rb5 59. c7 Rb7 { This also seemed like it was doing nothing for him. } 60. Kd8 { After this move he can't stop the promotion. } 60... Rxc7 { GG } (60... Rb8+ 61. cxb8=Q+) 61. Kxc7 Ke6 62. Rd2 Ke5 63. Kc6 Ke6 64. Re2+ Kf5 65. Kd6 Kf4 66. Kd5 Kf3 67. Re8 Kf4 68. Re7 Kf5 69. Rf7+ Kg4 70. Ke5 Kg3 71. Ke4 Kg4 72. Rg7+ Kh3 73. Kf4 Kh2 74. Kf3 Kh1 75. Kf2 Kh2 76. Rh7# 1-0


