1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 d6 4. Nf3 Nxe4 5. Nc3 Nxc3 6. dxc3 Be7 7. Bf4 { First move out of theory. Should have played Be3 instead. That said I struggle to see a big difference. } 7... O-O 8. Qd2 Nd7 9. O-O-O { This is all going according to plan. } 9... Nf6 10. Bd3 d5 11. h3 { I thought I was going to get yelled at for playing this move. But I really didn't see the urgency in playing anything else and preventing Bg4 seemed really nice. } 11... Ne4 { This I didn't understand. } 12. Bxe4 dxe4 { After this trade that pawn is very weak. } 13. Qxd8 { I decided to trade the queens off so I could make space for my knight to go to d2. Also since I was expecting to win a pawn I felt that trading queens was not a bad choice allowing me to enter an endgame up a pawn quite soon. } 13... Bxd8 14. Nd2 Bf5 15. Rhe1 { Increasing the number of attackers on the e4 pawn. } 15... Re8 16. f3 { And now this move secures that pawn for me since black can't take my f3 pawn: } 16... e3 { This I had actually failed to consider but when it happened I didn't really see the idea. The pawn is still lost. } (16... exf3 17. Rxe8#) 17. Bxe3 Bh4 { I had seen this move coming but Re2 seemed to completely avoid any danger. } 18. Re2 Bg5 19. Rde1 { Adding defenders was the only option since the bishop was pinned to the rook. } 19... Bh4 20. Bf2 { Here I was quite happy. I had looked at the few options black had and they all seemed better for me. Taking the bishops allows M2, moving the bishop from h4 allows M2 and taking my rook seemed fine. } 20... Rxe2 { Only move. } (20... Bxf2 21. Rxe8+ Rxe8 22. Rxe8#) (20... Bf6 21. Rxe8+ Rxe8 22. Rxe8#) 21. Rxe2 Bg5 22. Be3 { Here I went with this move because I was scared of the pressure black could create with Rd8 attacking my pinned knight. With this move Rd8 wasn't possible anymore but it did allow Re8. } 22... Re8 23. Nf1 { Here I felt like I was forced to play this move to defend my pinned bishop. } (23. Nc4 b5 { I thought this was completely losing. }) 23... Bd7 24. Kd1? { And here came my first big mistake. 23. ... Bd7 seemed like a move without a point to it. Bus obviously I missed the idea of going Bb5. } (24. b3 Bb5 25. c4) (24. c4 Bb5) 24... Bb5 { This hurt because it could have been so easily avoided with something like b3 and c4 or even c4 right away. } 25. Rd2 { Here I thought I was losing but not by a lot. } 25... Bf6 { Bf6 caught me off guard since now some threats are renewed by black and I couldn't find a great way to deal with everyone of them. } (25... Bxe3 26. Nxe3 Rxe3 27. Rd8+ Re8 28. Rxe8+ { This obviously wouldn't have worked out for black. }) (25... Bxf1 26. Bxg5 { This seemed great too as I was still up a pawn. }) 26. Re2 Bxe2+ 27. Kxe2 { Losing the exchange but I thought I had decent chances of holding this position. } 27... Bg5 28. Kd3 Bxe3 29. Nxe3 Rd8+ 30. Ke2 { Here I was quite unhappy but as I already mentioned definitely some hopes of holding this endgame. } 30... Kf8 31. b4 g6 32. a4 { Taking space on the queenside, I didn't see what else I could play for. } 32... h5 { And after this move my opponent offered a draw. There was no way I was going to win this and even trying to draw it would have been quite difficult in my opoinion. } 1/2-1/2


