1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 c5?! $146 { First move out of theory. Moving pawns instead of developing and creating a weakness in the backwards pawn on d6. } (5... Be7 { Only other move in my repertoire. }) 6. Bb5+! { I wanted my knight on f5 but I didn't want his bishop taking my knight right away. Also blocking with the knight seemed incorrect so the only move I thought made sense for him was Bd7. } 6... Bd7 { Only move in my opinion. } (6... Nc6 7. Bxc6+ (7. Nxc6 { This I thought would be better because I can't lose my bishop the same way I was losing my knight in the other line and also discovered check threat is almost always good. } 7... bxc6 8. Bxc6+ { Also this would have been great. }) 7... bxc6 8. Nxc6 { Winning a pawn but I thought I would lose my knight. } 8... Qb6 { Pretty sure knight is lost. }) 7. Nf5 { I quite liked this idea. My knight is much more of a threat on f5 than it would have been if I retreated to f3 for example. Also the bishop can't take the knight as it is pinned. } 7... Be7 (7... Bxb5 8. Nxb5 { I was keeping an eye on this potential trade but it seemed to only benefit me as I added an attacker on the d6 pawn and also created some threats on c7. } 8... Nxe4 9. Bf4 { Adding pressure on d6 } (9. Qe2 { Looking at it now this seems better since I don't think black can save the knight. })) 8. Bf4 { Developing and adding pressure on d6 } 8... O-O 9. Nxe7+?! { Here I think I tried to cash out too fast. I think castling would have been better as I then ended up having problems caused by my king still being in the middle. FIRST THING HIDE THE KING!!! } 9... Qxe7 10. Bxd6 { This was the idea. A skewer of the queen and bishop but my king still being in the middle of the board made this seem much less effective than I thought it would be. } 10... Qe6 11. O-O { I gave up on winning the exchange but I wanted to make sure black had little to no counterplay. } (11. Bxf8 Nxe4 { I saw this and didn't like it one bit. Hence why I chose to castle instead. } 12. Nxe4 Qxe4+ 13. Be2 Kxf8 (13... Qxg2 { I also saw this and thought I was not doing good here. } 14. Rf1 Kxf8)) 11... Rc8 12. e5 { Push knight win space. Also saw a potential for winning the d7 bishop. } 12... Ne8 13. Bxb8 Bxb5 { This saved his bishop and I had seen that this was his only hope of saving it but I thought my knight landing on b5 would benefit me. } 14. Nxb5 Rcxb8 { Only move as Raxb8 would have lost him the a7 pawn. } (14... Raxb8 15. Nxa7 Rd8 16. Qe2 $16) 15. Re1 { Defending the e5 pawn as it was the only advantage I had left. I was not very happy here. I felt like I had gone from having a strong dynamic advantage to only the static advantage of being a pawn up. } 15... Qb6 16. Nd6? { Thought moving my knight forward would give me some attacking ideas while retreating would have just lost me the b2 pawn. That said, for some reason, I missed Rd8. } 16... Rd8! { Initially once this move landed I thought I was just losing. So I decided to look for some dynamic moves that might give me some compensation. } 17. Qf3 { With the obvious threat of Qxf6. Also removing my queen from the pin of the rook. } 17... Nxd6 { I saw this as black's only move and I was quite happy with the resource I had found. } 18. exd6 Rxd6 19. Re7 { This again created a threat on f7 this time an even bigger threat. } 19... Rf6 { Here my plan was to play Qxb7. But I thought for a little longer and found Rae1. } (19... Re6 20. Qxf7+ Kh8 21. Rxe6 Qd8 22. Rae1 { This looked great, obviously. }) 20. Rae1 { This move threatened checkmate if black didn't defend the back rank. Or potentially a Queen vs 2 rooks endgame. } 20... Kf8 { A move I didn't see coming since I thought Qd8 was black's only move but it luckily didn't affect my plan. } (20... Qd8 21. Re8+ (21. Qxb7 { This is the move I would have chosen instead. }) 21... Qxe8 22. Rxe8+ Rxe8 { Normally I would have been happy with going into this but with the current threat of back rank mate and the attack on the queen I would have had to play some passive move and I didn't know if that would have been great. } 23. Qd1 { This would have been my move. } 23... Rfe6 { But this here looked very scary. I don't think I can save my queen. }) 21. Qxb7! { Protecting my pawn on b2 but more importantly threatening checkmate after Qxa8. } 21... Qxb7 { Only move I considered. } 22. Rxb7 Rb6 23. Ree7 { Doubled rooks on the 7th rank. I felt like I had misplayed the middle game but this endgame still felt very comfortable. } 23... Rxb7 24. Rxb7 Rd8 { Only move I really considered. } 25. Kf1 Rd2 26. c3 { Now the goal was to not blunder a single pawn and ideally win one or more of black's pawns. } 26... c4 27. a4 { Calculated some possible variations and it felt like having my pawn on a4 ensured its survival. } (27. h3) (27. b4 Rxa2 { This looked worse than if I'd have included a4 first. }) 27... Rd1+ { Didn't see this coming. } (27... Ke8 28. b4 cxb3 29. Rxb3) 28. Ke2 Ra1 { Here I considered Rb4 and Rxa7 only. } 29. Rxa7 (29. Rb4 Ra2 30. Kd2 a5! { This move was the reason I didn't choose Rb4. Where can my rook go now without black winning a pawn. }) 29... Ra2 30. Rb7 Rxa4 31. Rb4 { Offering the trade of rooks as I thought that would have been an easily winning king and pawn endgame. Also this created an attack on the c4 pawn. } 31... Ra2 32. Kd2 { Couldn't take c4 without losing b2. } (32. Rxc4 Rxb2+ { Was not sure this would have been a win. }) 32... Ke7 33. Kc2 Ke6 34. Rxc4 { And now two pawns up I didn't see a way to draw or lose. } 34... f5 35. Rb4 g5 { With the idea of getting my rook on a3. } 36. Rb3 h5 37. Ra3 { He allowed this but from here the game was won in my mind. } 37... Rxa3 38. bxa3 { Two isolated and passed pawns. Had they not been isolated I would have been happier but still great. } 38... Kd5 39. Kd3 { Get my king closer to his pawns just to be safe. } 39... g4 40. a4 h4 41. a5 f4 42. a6 { At some point he has to do something about my pawn... } 42... Kc6 43. Ke4 { And there it is. } 43... g3 44. hxg3 fxg3 45. fxg3 hxg3 46. Kf3 Kb6 47. Kxg3 Kxa6 48. Kf4 { An easily winning endgame as he can't stop both pawns. } 48... Kb5 49. g4 Kc4 50. g5 Kxc3 { And after this move he resigned. } 1-0


