al 0.02] } 16. Rad1 { [%eval -0.03] } { I thought for a while here as I knew I would have to move a rook but I didn't know which one and where. Eventually I picked this move since I couldn't find a concrete advantage with the other two rook moves and this one is more principled. 2 rooks in the center open files. } (16. Red1 { Other candidate. }) (16. Rac1 { Other candidate. }) 16... Rg6?! { [%eval 0.73] } { Inaccuracy. Bb4 was best. } (16... Bb4 17. Re3 Nc6 18. Nh5 Rg8 19. Nf6 Rh8 20. Bh6 c3 21. bxc3 Bc5 22. Re2) 17. Ne8?? { [%eval -2.86] } { Blunder. Nxh7 was best. } { I really hate free pawns I guess... } (17. Nxh7 b5 18. Bxd8 Kxd8 19. Nhg5 Kc8 20. Nxe6 Rxe6 21. Rxe6 fxe6 22. g4 Kd7) 17... h6?? { [%eval 0.64] } { Blunder. Bg4 was best. } { This move surprised me but it seemed to not work that well for black. } (17... Bg4 18. Nxd6+ (18. h4 Bxf3 19. gxf3 h6 20. f4 hxg5 21. f5 Rg8 22. Nf6 Rf8 23. h5) 18... Rxd6 { Since black could now take back with the rook. }) 18. Nxd6+ { [%eval 0.68] } { My "attack" kind of failed. I didn't find anything winning and this seemed like a way to win back the pawn. While leaving black with a very uncoordinated position. } 18... cxd6 { [%eval 0.55] } 19. Bxd8?! { [%eval -0.27] } { Inaccuracy. Be7 was best. } { Wanted to remove the bishop from the attack of the pawn and I liked that I would then be taking the pawn back with check. } (19. Be7 Bg4 20. Rxd6 Rxd6 21. Bxd6 Kd7 22. Ne5+ Kxd6 23. Nxg4 h5 24. Ne3 b5) 19... Kxd8 { [%eval -0.24] } 20. Ne5 { [%eval -0.47] } { This looked better than Rxd6 right away. It forces black to move the rook and allows me to have a more active knight after I take on d6 which turned out to be very true as that knight was a beauty in the endgame. } (20. Rxd6+ { This was my original plan but then I stopped for a bit to see if I could find something better. }) 20... Rg8 { [%eval -0.46] } 21. Rxd6+ { [%eval -0.66] } 21... Kc7 { [%eval -0.76] } 22. Red1 { [%eval -0.69] } { Maybe should have retreated instead but I was hoping she would maybe blunder something. } 22... Rad8 { [%eval -0.69] } { That said this is the move she went for and I saw no way to avoid the trade of rooks. } (22... a6 { For example... } 23. Nxf7 Bxf7 24. Rd7+ Kb6 25. Rxf7 { I could win a pawn like this if black did nothing. }) 23. Rxd8 { [%eval -0.65] } (23. Nxc4 { I considered this. } 23... Bxc4 (23... Rxd6 24. Rxd6 { Here I lose everything } (24. Nxd6 Rd8 { And here I lose everything too })) 24. Rxd8 Rxd8 25. Rc1 { But here my rook is pinned to the back rank. }) 23... Rxd8 { [%eval -0.61] } { Last chance to keep a rook in the game but I didn't see anywhere it would be useful. } 24. Rxd8 { [%eval -0.58] } 24... Kxd8 { [%eval -0.49] } { Knight vs Bishop endgame. I have studied these 0. I had the feeling that her bishop should be better as it's a bishop and can move faster around the board. But I thought that if I think a lot I could find ways to make my knight annoying. } 25. a3 { [%eval -0.64] } { Only move I checked with engine before analyzing and was very happy to see it's the best move. } (25. h3 { for example... } 25... c3 { I thought this would be good for black. } 26. bxc3 Bxa2 { Now they have a protected outside passed pawn which would have sucked. }) 25... Kc7 { [%eval -0.73] } 26. f4 { [%eval -0.6] } { Lock the knight there and create a path for my king. The only issue being f6 but then I thought retreating my knight to f3 or advancing to g6 would be interesting. } 26... h5 { [%eval -0.13] } { This didn't make much sense to me and seemed like a loss of time. } 27. Kf2 { [%eval -0.12] } { Finally bringing the king. } 27... b5 { [%eval 0.0] } { Good move to defend the weak c4 pawn and potentially play a5 and b4 in the future. } 28. Ke3 { [%eval 0.16] } 28... Kd6 { [%eval 0.37] } 29. h3?! { [%eval -0.23] } { Inaccuracy. Kd4 was best. } { Wasn't super happy after I played this move. Felt like g2 was now weak should have maybe played g3. } (29. Kd4 Bd5 30. g3 a6 31. Nd7 f5 32. Ne5 a5 33. Ng6 Be6 34.